.TH eroosterctl-user-exists 1 "June 2026" "eroosterctl" "Erooster Manual"
.SH NAME
eroosterctl\-user\-exists \- check if a mail user exists
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eroosterctl user exists
\fIemail\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Checks whether \fIemail\fR is registered in the database. Produces no output;
communicates the result via the exit code. This makes it suitable for use in
shell conditionals, Ansible \fBfailed_when\fR, and CI scripts.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fIemail\fR
Email address to look up (required positional argument).
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
# Shell conditional
if eroosterctl user exists alice@example.com; then
    echo "User exists"
else
    echo "User not found"
fi

# Ansible
- name: Check user exists
  command: eroosterctl user exists alice@example.com
  register: result
  failed_when: result.rc not in [0, 1]
  changed_when: false
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
User exists.
.TP
\fB1\fR
User does not exist.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBeroosterctl\-user\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-user\-add\fR(1)
